Percy Tau of South Africa challenged by Jardel Nazane of Sao Tome during the 2021 Afcon Qualifier match between Sao Tome and South Africa at the Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium, Port Elizabeth on the 16 November 2020. PORT ELIZABETH - South Africa defeated São Tomé and Príncipe 4-2 in an Afcon qualifier match at the Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium in Port Elizabeth on Monday afternoon. Themba Zwane and Percy Tau scored twice for Bafana Bafana who had fallen behind when Sao Tome took an early lead. Molefi Ntseki's team are now level on nine points with group C leaders Ghana but the Black Stars have a game in hand, they are away to Sudan on Tuesday. READ: TV blackout for Bafana game Meanwhile, Bafana Bafana's match against Sao Tome was not broadcast on South African television. This is after the SABC could not reach a formal agreement with Sao Tome, who held the rights as it was technically their home game.